evidence.phenotypeFreeText:
Pervasive mucocutaneous-immunodeficiency syndrome of EV-HPV, HSV-1, leprosy. Late onset - 7 years old.
Common to both P1 and P2: (
1) moderate lymphopenia of total absolute lymphocyte counts; 
(2) mildly low CD3+CD4+ T-cell absolute counts; 
(3) nearly absent “naïve” CD4CD45RA+ T cells ; 
(4) a preponderance of double-negative (DN) CD3+CD4-CD8- T-cells, verified as Υδ T-cell subpopulation in P2 and expressed as 100 % of the DN T-cells; 
(5) undetectable memory B cells;
(6) low NK cell absolute counts; 
(7) modestly suppressed mitogen-induced lymphoproliferation, particularly to ConA and PHA;
(8) an elevated serum IgE (peak levels at onset of presentation of their clinical diseases)
